<subSubSection id="C30EFBC0FF87FFC6B4363599FB52FE0D" box="[1078,1188,435,456]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF87FFC6B4363599FB52FE0D" blockId="11.[1078,1188,435,456]" box="[1078,1188,435,456]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">
<heading id="D0E31F27FF87FFC6B4363599FB52FE0D" box="[1078,1188,435,456]" centered="true" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" reason="8">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B4363599FB52FE0D" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[1078,1188,435,456]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">PEPSINAE</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30EFBC0FF87FFC6B33A35F3FB84F991" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF87FFC6B33A35F3FA54FBB8" blockId="11.[826,1442,473,1902]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A35F3FC55FE25" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[826,931,473,495]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
is also a diverse group with a conflicting history of classification, and several genera of uncertain membership. For example, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B4A8363CFACEFDE1" box="[1192,1336,534,555]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Epipompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B4A8363CFACEFDE1" box="[1192,1336,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Epipompilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously considered a monotypic subfamily (
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B53A361FFC87FDA0" author="Shimizu A" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref12270" refString="Shimizu A. 1994. Phylogeny and classification of the family Pompilidae (Hymenoptera). Tokyo Metropolitan University Bulletin of Natural History 2: 1 - 142." type="journal article" year="1994">Shimizu, 1994</bibRefCitation>
), and then transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B48D367EFC8BFD42" authority="(Pitts et al., 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Pitts" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">
Ctenocerinae (
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B52B367EFC83FD42" author="Pitts JP &amp; Wasbauer MS &amp; von Dohlen CD" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="63 - 84" refId="ref11898" refString="Pitts JP, Wasbauer MS, von Dohlen CD. 2006. Preliminary morphological analysis of relationships between the spider wasp subfamilies (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae): revisiting an old problem. Zoologica Scripta 35: 63 - 84." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pitts 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B566367EFA62FDA3" box="[1382,1428,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. More recently, cladistic morphological analyses with qualitative and quantitative characters suggested 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B3873685FBE4FD0E" box="[903,1042,687,708]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Epipompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B3873685FBE4FD0E" box="[903,1042,687,708]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Epipompilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be the sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B4DF369AFA57FD0F" authority="Banks" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1934" box="[1247,1441,687,709]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Minagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B4DF369AFAA2FD0F" box="[1247,1364,688,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Minagenia</emphasis>
Banks
</taxonomicName>
(E. F. Santos, pers. comm.). 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B48D36E5FAF1FD2E" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1934" box="[1165,1287,719,740]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Minagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B48D36E5FAF1FD2E" box="[1165,1287,719,740]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Minagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has suffered similar inconsistencies. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B45736C7FAD9FCC9" box="[1111,1327,749,771]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Minagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B45736C7FB24FCC8" box="[1111,1234,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Minagenia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are morphologically homogeneous, but difficult to assign to a subfamily (
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B3C13700FB71FC8A" author="Dreisbach RR" box="[961,1159,810,832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="832 - 845" refId="ref10760" refString="Dreisbach RR. 1953. New species in the genera Dipogon Fox and Minagenia Banks (Hymenoptera: Psammocharidae) with keys to species and photomicrographs of genital parts. American Midland Naturalist 49: 832 - 845." type="journal article" year="1953">Dreisbach, 1953</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B49F3700FABCFC8A" author="Townes H" box="[1183,1354,810,832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref12461" refString="Townes H. 1957. Neartic wasps of the subfamilies Pepsinae and Ceropalinae. United Sates National Museum Bulletin 209: 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="1957">Townes (1957)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A3763FC46FC94" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1934" box="[826,944,841,862]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Minagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B33A3763FC46FC94" box="[826,944,841,862]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Minagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B3D63762FBA8FC94" authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1888" box="[982,1118,840,862]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ceropalinae">Ceropalinae</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B4683763FB08FC94" author="Haupt H" box="[1128,1278,840,862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref11332" refString="Haupt H. 1959. Elemente einer systematischen Aufteilung der Macromerinae m. (Hymenoptera-Sphecoidea): Fam. Pompilidae, Subfam. Macromerinae. Nova Acta Leopoldina Leipzig 21: 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1959">Haupt (1959)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B5093763FA6BFC94" author="Evans HE" box="[1289,1437,840,862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="212 - 226" refId="ref11080" refString="Evans HE. 1973. Studies on Neotropical Pompilidae (Hymenoptera). The genera of Auplopodini. Psyche 80: 212 - 226." type="journal article" year="1973">Evans (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B373374DFBBAFCB7" author="Pitts JP &amp; Wasbauer MS &amp; von Dohlen CD" box="[883,1100,871,893]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="63 - 84" refId="ref11898" refString="Pitts JP, Wasbauer MS, von Dohlen CD. 2006. Preliminary morphological analysis of relationships between the spider wasp subfamilies (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae): revisiting an old problem. Zoologica Scripta 35: 63 - 84." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pitts 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B3BA3742FC1BFCB6" box="[954,1005,871,893]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
considered it a member of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A37AFFC5CFC51" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[826,938,901,923]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
. Another example concerns the variable 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A378EFAA1FC70" authority="Haliday. Roig Alsina (1989)" authorityName="Haliday. Roig Alsina" authorityYear="1989" box="[826,1367,932,954]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Chirodamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B33A378EFC25FC73" box="[826,979,932,953]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Chirodamus</emphasis>
Haliday. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B45F378EFAA1FC70" author="Roig Alsina A" box="[1119,1367,932,954]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="165 - 170" refId="ref12126" refString="Roig Alsina A. 1989. La posicion sistematica de los grupos hasta ahora incluidos en Chirodamus Haliday sensu lato y revision de Pompilocalus gen. nov. (Hymenoptera Pompilidae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologia de Argentina 43: 165 - 170." type="journal article" year="1989">Roig Alsina (1989)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
split 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A37E9FC31FC12" authorityName="Haliday. Roig Alsina" authorityYear="1989" box="[826,967,963,984]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Chirodamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B33A37E9FC31FC12" box="[826,967,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Chirodamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into six Neotropical genera: 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B51437E9FCABFC3D" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B51437E9FA57FC12" authorityName="Haliday. Roig Alsina" authorityYear="1989" box="[1300,1441,963,984]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Chirodamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Chirodamus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A253C922FF87FFC6B33A37C8FCABFC3D" box="[826,861,994,1015]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B36C37CBFB77FC3D" authority="Roig Alsina" authorityName="Roig Alsina" box="[876,1153,993,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Plagicurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B36C37CBFC05FC3C" box="[876,1011,993,1014]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Plagicurgus</emphasis>
Roig Alsina
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B48D37CBFA6BFC3D" authority="Ashmead" authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1900" box="[1165,1437,993,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Calopompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B48D37CBFADFFC3C" box="[1165,1321,993,1014]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Calopompilus</emphasis>
Ashmead
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A302AFA9BFBDC" authority="Roig Alsina, Aimatocares Roig Alsina" authorityName="Roig Alsina, Aimatocares Roig Alsina" box="[826,1389,1024,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pompilocalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B33A302AFC3AFBDF" box="[826,972,1024,1045]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Pompilocalus</emphasis>
Roig Alsina, 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B45F302AFB10FBDF" box="[1119,1254,1024,1045]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Aimatocares</emphasis>
Roig Alsina
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A3034FBB7FBFE" authority="Banks." authorityName="Banks." box="[826,1089,1054,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Anacyphononyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B33A3034FC1CFBF9" box="[826,1002,1054,1075]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Anacyphononyx</emphasis>
Banks.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B4483034FB09FBFE" box="[1096,1279,1054,1076]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B4483034FB22FBF9" authorityName="Haliday. Roig Alsina" authorityYear="1989" box="[1096,1236,1054,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Chirodamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Chirodamus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A253C922FF87FFC6B4DC3035FB09FBFE" box="[1244,1279,1055,1076]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A3017FC4CFB99" baseAuthorityName="Arnold" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[826,954,1085,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pompilinae">Pompilinae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B3E53017FB5DFB99" author="Pitts JP &amp; Wasbauer MS &amp; von Dohlen CD" box="[997,1195,1085,1107]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="63 - 84" refId="ref11898" refString="Pitts JP, Wasbauer MS, von Dohlen CD. 2006. Preliminary morphological analysis of relationships between the spider wasp subfamilies (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae): revisiting an old problem. Zoologica Scripta 35: 63 - 84." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pitts 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B4233014FBA5FB98" box="[1059,1107,1085,1107]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, but the other genera of 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B3573076FBFAFBBB" box="[855,1036,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B3573076FC12FBBB" authorityName="Haliday. Roig Alsina" authorityYear="1989" box="[855,996,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Chirodamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">Chirodamus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A253C922FF87FFC6B3EC3076FBFAFBBB" box="[1004,1036,1116,1137]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have been considered as 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B5333076FA6BFBB8" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[1331,1437,1116,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF87FFC6B3533050FB84F991" blockId="11.[826,1442,473,1902]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">
Our results recovered a monophyletic 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B5183050FA89FB5A" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[1304,1407,1146,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
in the relaxed-clock analysis only, with good support. Most of the deeper relationships within this clade were not supported, whereas several lineages of more recent origin were highly supported. The molecular phylogeny supports the assignment of the controversial genera, discussed above, as members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B4983118FAF4FA82" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[1176,1282,1330,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B5103118FA57FA8D" box="[1296,1441,1330,1351]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Epipompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B5103118FA57FA8D" box="[1296,1441,1330,1351]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Epipompilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is monophyletic, although its position within 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B53B317AFA57FAAC" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[1339,1441,1360,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
is ambiguous. It has a disjunct distribution, with species found in the Neotropics and Australasia. In our molecular phylogeny and in a morphological phylogenetic study (E. F. Santos, pers. comm.), 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B4CB31E1FAAAFA2A" box="[1227,1372,1483,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Epipompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B4CB31E1FAAAFA2A" box="[1227,1372,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Epipompilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recovered as two major clades, one Neotropical and the other Australasian. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B4243222FB43F9D7" box="[1060,1205,1544,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Epipompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B4243222FB43F9D7" box="[1060,1205,1544,1565]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Epipompilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hunt spiders inside their burrows and permanently paralyse them before oviposition (
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC6B3C7326FFB93F991" author="Pollard SD" box="[967,1125,1605,1627]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="37 - 39" refId="ref11939" refString="Pollard SD. 1982. Epipompilis insularis (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae), a parasitoid of hunting spiders. New Zealand Journal of Zoology 9: 37 - 39." type="journal article" year="1982">Pollard, 1982</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30EFBC0FF87FFC1B353324EFD52FF30" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="283" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF87FFC1B353324EFD52FF30" blockId="11.[826,1442,473,1902]" lastBlockId="12.[144,759,198,1719]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="283" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">
Our analyses also support 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B472324EFB13F9B3" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1934" box="[1138,1253,1636,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Minagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B472324EFB13F9B3" box="[1138,1253,1636,1657]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Minagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B51C324EFCAFF95D" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B51C324EFA54F9B3" authorityName="Haliday. Roig Alsina" authorityYear="1989" box="[1308,1442,1636,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Chirodamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">Chirodamus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A253C922FF87FFC6B33A32A8FCAFF95D" box="[826,857,1666,1687]" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
as members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B40832A8FB99F952" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[1032,1135,1666,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B47A32A9FB06F952" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1934" box="[1146,1264,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Minagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B47A32A9FB06F952" box="[1146,1264,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Minagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is strongly supported as monophyletic, but its position within 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B53E328BFA57F97D" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[1342,1441,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
is uncertain. Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B45832EAFB24F91F" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1934" box="[1112,1234,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Minagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF87FFC6B45832EAFB24F91F" box="[1112,1234,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="282">Minagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF87FFC6B33A32F4FC57F93E" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[826,929,1758,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
by having a straight stinger, a compressed metasoma, bifid claws and the veins 2 r-m and 3 r-m continuously curved outward and with similar appearance. They are ectoparasitoids, paralysing their prey only temporarily. Our results also confirm 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF87FFC1B5123372FF21FF16" author="Roig Alsina A" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="283" pageId="11" pageNumber="282" pagination="165 - 170" refId="ref12126" refString="Roig Alsina A. 1989. La posicion sistematica de los grupos hasta ahora incluidos en Chirodamus Haliday sensu lato y revision de Pompilocalus gen. nov. (Hymenoptera Pompilidae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologia de Argentina 43: 165 - 170." type="journal article" year="1989">Roig Alsina’s (1989)</bibRefCitation>
division of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B15E34ECFE1DFF11" authorityName="Haliday. Roig Alsina" authorityYear="1989" box="[350,491,198,219]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Chirodamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B15E34ECFE1DFF11" box="[350,491,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Chirodamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into several genera (to the extent that we have sampled these taxa).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30EFBC0FF80FFC1B0A83529FD4EF97D" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF80FFC1B0A83529FD84FAE3" blockId="12.[144,759,198,1719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">
Amongst 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B11E3529FE7CFED3" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[286,394,259,281]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
tribes, the most morphologically and behaviourally diverse is 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B2133508FD78FEF2" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1912" box="[531,654,290,312]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ageniellini">Ageniellini</taxonomicName>
(clade L, excluding 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B105356AFE79FE9F" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" box="[261,399,320,341]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Cyphononyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B105356AFE79FE9F" box="[261,399,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Cyphononyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B27A356AFD00FE9C" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1912" box="[634,758,320,342]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ageniellini">Ageniellini</taxonomicName>
was recovered by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF80FFC1B1633575FDE0FEBF" author="Shimizu A" box="[355,534,351,373]" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref12270" refString="Shimizu A. 1994. Phylogeny and classification of the family Pompilidae (Hymenoptera). Tokyo Metropolitan University Bulletin of Natural History 2: 1 - 142." type="journal article" year="1994">Shimizu (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF80FFC1B2253575FD05FEBF" author="Pitts JP &amp; Wasbauer MS &amp; von Dohlen CD" box="[549,755,351,373]" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" pagination="63 - 84" refId="ref11898" refString="Pitts JP, Wasbauer MS, von Dohlen CD. 2006. Preliminary morphological analysis of relationships between the spider wasp subfamilies (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae): revisiting an old problem. Zoologica Scripta 35: 63 - 84." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pitts 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B2663575FD61FEBE" box="[614,663,351,372]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF80FFC1B0C03557FDACFE5E" author="Shimizu A &amp; Wasbauer MS &amp; Takami Y" box="[192,602,381,404]" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" pagination="88 - 117" refId="ref12335" refString="Shimizu A, Wasbauer MS, Takami Y. 2010. Phylogeny and the evolution of nesting behaviour in the tribe Ageniellini (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 160: 88 - 117." type="journal article" year="2010">Shimizu, Wasbauer &amp; Takami (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, but this tribe is made paraphyletic in our analyses by the position of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B0AE3591FEB7FE1A" authorityName="Wahis, Durand &amp; Villemant" authorityYear="2009" box="[174,321,443,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Melanagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B0AE3591FEB7FE1A" box="[174,321,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Melanagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B1523591FE13FE1A" authorityName="Wahis, Durand &amp; Villemant" authorityYear="2009" box="[338,485,443,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Melanagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B1523591FE13FE1A" box="[338,485,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Melanagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF80FFC1B0B135F3FDC0FE25" author="Wahis R &amp; Durand F &amp; Villemant C" box="[177,566,473,495]" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" pagination="707 - 718" refId="ref12515" refString="Wahis R, Durand F, Villemant C. 2009. Pompiles de l'ile d'Espiritu Santo, Vanuatu (Insecta, Hymenoptera, Pompilidae). Zoosystema 31: 707 - 718." type="journal article" year="2009">Wahis, Durand &amp; Villemant (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, and was defined and placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B13F35D2FE48FDC4" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1912" box="[319,446,504,526]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ageniellini">Ageniellini</taxonomicName>
by having the metasoma petiolate and by the first tergite lacking a transverse carina. Our results indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B216361FFD5FFD80" authorityName="Wahis, Durand &amp; Villemant" authorityYear="2009" box="[534,681,565,586]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Melanagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B216361FFD5FFD80" box="[534,681,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Melanagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unrelated to other 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B1413679FE4AFDA3" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1912" box="[321,444,595,617]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ageniellini">Ageniellini</taxonomicName>
. Rather, it emerges as sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B0AC3658FEBEFD4D" authorityName="Kohl" authorityYear="1884" box="[172,328,626,647]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B0AC3658FEBEFD4D" box="[172,328,626,647]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Sphictostethus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B1D53658FD97FD4D" authorityName="Wahis, Durand &amp; Villemant" authorityYear="2009" box="[469,609,626,647]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Melanagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B1D53658FD97FD4D" box="[469,609,626,647]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Melanagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares states of facial characters (lack of malar space with eyes touching mandibles and a clypeus somewhat rectangular and convex), pronotal characters (rounded with a deep sulcus laterally), and wing-venation characters. However, as 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B0903721FE8DFCEB" box="[144,379,779,801]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Melanagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B0903721FED5FCEA" box="[144,291,779,800]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Melanagenia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
lack a carina on the first tergite and have a petiolate metasoma, these two character states – although useful in identifying 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B2443762FD48FC94" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1912" box="[580,702,840,862]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ageniellini">Ageniellini</taxonomicName>
taxa – can no longer be considered unique synapomorphies of the tribe. The observation that 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B21D37AFFD00FC51" authority="Banks" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1933" box="[541,758,901,923]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Phanagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B21D37AFFD53FC50" box="[541,677,901,922]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Phanagenia</emphasis>
Banks
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B097378EFEE5FC70" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1912" box="[151,275,932,954]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ageniellini">Ageniellini</taxonomicName>
) possesses a carina on the first metasomal segment further undermines the diagnostic value of this metasomal character. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B1E037CBFD8DFC3C" authorityName="Wahis, Durand &amp; Villemant" authorityYear="2009" box="[480,635,993,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Melanagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B1E037CBFD8DFC3C" box="[480,635,993,1014]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Melanagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is herein removed from 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B12F302AFE51FBDC" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1912" box="[303,423,1024,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ageniellini">Ageniellini</taxonomicName>
and placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B24C302AFD57FBDC" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[588,673,1024,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pepsini">Pepsini</taxonomicName>
. As discussed above (see 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B15A3034FE19FBFE" box="[346,495,1054,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">Ctenocerinae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B2013034FD6EFBF9" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" box="[513,664,1054,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Lepidocnemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B2013034FD6EFBF9" box="[513,664,1054,1075]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Lepidocnemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B0AB3017FECCFB98" box="[171,314,1085,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pompilocalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B0AB3017FECCFB98" box="[171,314,1085,1106]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Pompilocalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B1713017FE02FB98" box="[369,500,1085,1106]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Aimatocares</emphasis>
, within a larger lineage including 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B0FB3076FE61FBBB" authorityName="Kohl" authorityYear="1884" box="[251,407,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B0FB3076FE61FBBB" box="[251,407,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">Sphictostethus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF80FFC1B1CD3076FD00FBBB" box="[461,758,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B1CD3076FDADFBBB" authorityName="Wahis, Durand &amp; Villemant" authorityYear="2009" box="[461,603,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Melanagenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanagenia</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B2643076FD00FBBB" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" box="[612,758,1116,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Lepidocnemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lepidocnemis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is the only representative of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B2623050FD01FB5A" box="[610,759,1146,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">Ctenocerinae</taxonomicName>
in our study and is herein transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B28830B3FD05FB65" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[648,755,1177,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B090309DFF15FB07" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[144,227,1207,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pepsini">Pepsini</taxonomicName>
and the other tribes are in dire need of further studies and redefinition of most of their taxa. Our samples and analyses are not sufficient to make further nomenclatural decisions regarding tribes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF80FFC1B0A83118FD4EF97D" blockId="12.[144,759,198,1719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="283">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF80FFC1B0A83118FEFDFA82" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[168,267,1330,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
(clade D) are now defined by: (1) metasomal sternum 2 with a distinct sharp transverse groove; (2) the mesofemur and the metafemur without subapical spine-like setae set in grooves or pits; (3) the metatibia with apical spine-like setae of uniform length, the setae not splayed; and (4) the fore wing with vein Cu1 simple at base, without any definite downward deflection, such that the second discal cell (2D) is without a ‘pocket’ posterior. A broad range of nesting behaviour occurs within this subfamily, including nesting in preexisting cavities, using the spider’s burrow, digging a burrow in the ground, building nests of mud, and behaving as true parasitoids and kleptoparasites.
</paragraph>
